programme.desc: The Gloucester, Massachusetts's bluefin tuna fishing fleet is back for another season with the biggest paydays they've ever seen and the most toxic voyages in Wicked Tuna history. FV-Tuna.Com is determined to reclaim the title of Champion of the fleet. With his returning, trusty crew, Captain Dave Carraro plans to start this season by catching the first fish and not stop until he has brought in more fish and more profit than any other boat. But, he'll have stiff competition this year fishing against the best of the best in New England. All boats are returning: as the second place finisher last season, Pinwheel is on a mission to dethrone the champion; Hot Tuna has a renewed sense of purpose, longing to shatter their lackluster reputation; Hard Merchandise is expanding its family operation with a new crew-member ready to make a profit; Wicked Pissah needs to retain and surpass its successful previous season; and Fish Hawk desperately needs to recover from an embarrassing and u.

He realizes his window for getting meat is quickly closing and a winter struggling for protein would be excruciating. In a remote spot in southern Utah, Matt returns home to his pit house to discover the land has changed. He needs to check his resources and assess if he’ll have enough to survive through the colder months.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E7
programme.desc: Thorn goes on a nutria hunt hoping to provide protein that Delia and he need to survive, Tony and Amelia take a big step in their homesteading journey and attempt to sell goods at market in town, Colbert is in the midst of a natural disaster as rising waters put his new cabin construction at risk, and Matt goes on a turkey hunt in the canyons he now calls home.

Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

Their mission is to cure their own medical ailments that they have struggled to fix at home.

Featuring original interviews with the DEA agents, Colombian police officers, drug smugglers, and politicians who hunted and were hunted by Escobar, this episode is equally an intimate portrait and cautionary tale of one man's unchecked megalomania - and his struggle to overcome adversity.

programme.title: Inside Incredible Machines E6
programme.desc: For forty years, Nimitz class aircraft carriers have delivered US military might wherever it is needed, anywhere on the globe. But now, this legendary design is being phased out and new carriers are planned. But until they're ready, the giant Nimitz ships have to be kept at the forefront of military technology. In this episode, engineer and host Chad Zdenek spends a week on board the USS Carl Vinson to work with the highly trained specialist engineers, mechanics and sailors who keep this incredible floating city in perfect working order during a critical mission in the Pacific - training twenty F18 pilots who have never taken off from an Aircraft Carrier before. This gives Chad the chance to discover the five engineering innovations at the heart of America's most incredible Aircraft Carrier.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E8
programme.desc: On its final approach to Zurich, Alitalia Flight 404 plows into a forested hillside killing everyone on board. Checking the DC-9's radar track, Swiss investigators immediately notice the aircraft was flying too low. But closer analysis of the evidence only deepens the mystery. Did a hidden flaw in the navigation system lead two pilots down a deadly path?

programme.title: Jane Goodall: The Hope
programme.desc: Dr, Jane Goodall arrived at a 1986 conference as a scientist and-after learning the extent of the threat facing chimpanzees-left as an activist. The film begins with this critical transformation and follows Jane through three decades of advocacy work. Jane knew she must take action to protect chimps and other animals living in the wild, to improve the well being of chimps in captivity and to inspire a young generation of change makers for this vital work to continue. In a moment in which the environmental crisis can seem overwhelming, Jane has made it her mission to encourage us all that solutions are within reach. Our cameras capture Jane as she travels over 300 days a year, meeting with everyone from schoolchildren in Zanzibar to Silicon Valley tech giants to Prince Harry, using wisdom, heart and humor to spread a message of hope and show that every individual has the potential be a catalyst and create lasting change.

programme.title: Photo Ark: Rarest Creatures
programme.desc: Join National Geographic photographer Joel Sartore as he travels to Madagascar, China, the Czech Republic, and New Zealand, to photograph creatures found nowhere else on the planet, and add them to his Photo Ark.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E4
programme.desc: Oil worker Steve has owned his Aston Martin DB6 for over 20 years. After buying it for a bargain price the car became his pride and joy but when it broke down his attempts to repair the Aston failed. Since then a serious fall and chronic health problems have taken their toll and restoring the British classic is now out of his reach. While Fuzz struggles with an engine that hasn't turned over in 20 years Tim will have to do his best to get all the right Aston parts which are notoriously expensive.

programme.title: To Catch A Smuggler: USA E5
programme.desc: JFK CBP stops a passenger traveling from Trinidad transporting cans of tropical fruit. But instead of fruit, the inspecting officer discovers a white powdery substance. In the Miami mail facility, CBP finds vials of a suspicious liquid which tests for GBL, a dangerous date rape drug. HSI conducts a controlled delivery hoping to arrest the smuggler. In LAX, CBP questions female passengers who might be victims of sex trafficking and marriage fraud.

programme.title: Deadly Drops E2
programme.desc: DEADLY DROPS: TRAPPED IN AN ELEVATOR takes us into the fascinating world of lifts and the looks at terrifying moments when these everyday machines suddenly cause chaos. Capable of taking people captive, trapping passengers in doors and suddenly plummeting down shafts, this film meets some of the people who have been most badly affected by lift malfunctions.

programme.title: New Orleans: City Of Stories
programme.desc: Delving into the history and culture of the Big Easy. This special showcases some of the best when local storytellers reveal the secrets of what unfolds behind its courtyard walls and ornate facades.

programme.title: Living Free With Kimi Werner E1
programme.desc: Champion spear fisher Kimi Werner visits a woman living a largely subsistence way of life and learns about her lifestyle. She's in pursuit of a deep truth about what it means to live more simply, more freely, and with a closer connection to nature.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5 Compilations E10
programme.desc: Over the past four seasons, our fleet has caught over 27 tons of bluefin tuna and put almost a million dollars in their pockets. Now we're letting you the viewer play the buyer. Let's get a tail cut and a core sample ready, because we're putting your 'tuna expertise' to the test. Can you spot the heaviest, the longest and most valuable fish in the history of 'Wicked Tuna: North vs South'?

programme.title: Silk Railroad E1
programme.desc: The Belt and Road Initiative is connecting China to Europe in a bid to boost trade connections with the west. Yiwu, an inland city 300km from Shanghai, is a terminus on this east-west trade network which has been dubbed the new Silk Railroad. One of the wealthiest cities in China, Yiwu made its riches through the sale of knick- knacks. In 2016 alone, it exported exporting over $25.6 billion worth of goods. With this new transportation network that transports goods to Europe in 16 days as compared to one year via the ancient silk road, historian Sam Willis and ChInese journalist Li Qiuyuan want to explore how this new railway is rehashing Yiwu's trading heritage and how it's changing how Yiwu trades with the west.

programme.title: Silk Railroad E2
programme.desc: 2000 years ago, in the time of the ancient Silk Road, the journey between China, Central Asia and Europe often took an entire year. Today, goods can be transported overland in just 14 days thanks to the world's longest rail service, a 13,000 KM route that connects China and Europe. Now, with ancient connections being revived for the 21st century, historian Sam Willis and journalist Li Qiuyuan travel to Chengdu, to explore how a new era of trade is shaping the city.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S17E8

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E13
programme.sub-title: Seven Wonders Of The New World
programme.desc: The young Carl Sagan and Neil Tyson first discovered their passion for science at the NY World's Fairs of the past. We visit the dazzling Pavilions of the 2039 NY World's Fair, where problems we currently think intractable have been plausibly solved through public commitment and scientific imagination. And our baby is a woman now, with a baby of her own and a future bright with possibilities.

programme.title: Paris To Pittsburgh
programme.desc: Paris to Pittsburgh brings to life the impassioned efforts of individuals who are battling the most severe threats of climate change in their own backyards. Set against the national debate over the United States' energy future - and the Trump administration's explosive decision to exit the Paris Climate Agreement - the film captures what's at stake for communities around the country and the inspiring ways Americans are responding.

programme.title: Science Of Stupid S6E20
programme.desc: In this episode we learn about motorcycle flips, how to avoid hurt when attempting to parkour lache, and how to avoid humiliation when walking up stairs.

programme.title: Genius S2E1
programme.desc: Pablo Picasso (Antonio Banderas) struggles to bring attention to the rising threat of fascism in Spain. Meanwhile, Young Pablo (Alex Rich) dreams of becoming a great painter. But first he must find his own voice.

programme.title: Cosmos: Possible Worlds E12
programme.sub-title: Coming Of Age In The Anthropocene
programme.desc: What kind of world can a child born in 2020 expect to grow up in? And when did our slide into planet-wide environmental destruction begin? The possible world that awaits our baby girl into her 20's: one darkened by our refusal to face the real and mounting challenges we face but concluding with a message of hope.

Did a hidden flaw in the navigation system lead two pilots down a deadly path?

programme.title: Silk Railroad E1
programme.desc: The Belt and Road Initiative is connecting China to Europe in a bid to boost trade connections with the west. Yiwu, an inland city 300km from Shanghai, is a terminus on this east-west trade network which has been dubbed the new Silk Railroad. One of the wealthiest cities in China, Yiwu made its riches through the sale of knick- knacks. In 2016 alone, it exported exporting over $25.6 billion worth of goods. With this new transportation network that transports goods to Europe in 16 days as compared to one year via the ancient silk road, historian Sam Willis and ChInese journalist Li Qiuyuan want to explore how this new railway is rehashing Yiwu's trading heritage and how it's changing how Yiwu trades with the west.

programme.title: Silk Railroad E2
programme.desc: 2000 years ago, in the time of the ancient Silk Road, the journey between China, Central Asia and Europe often took an entire year. Today, goods can be transported overland in just 14 days thanks to the world's longest rail service, a 13,000 KM route that connects China and Europe. Now, with ancient connections being revived for the 21st century, historian Sam Willis and journalist Li Qiuyuan travel to Chengdu, to explore how a new era of trade is shaping the city.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E6
programme.desc: On an adventure through Central America, Tom Hart Dyke and Paul Winder are kidnapped and have a $3 million price tag placed on their heads. They reluctantly decide to return to their captors for proper directions, although they are warned if they do, their heads will roll.

Presenting the MEGA facts of the kitchen, 25,000 children are fed 3 meals a day (approx. 76000 in total) in a 10,000-capacity dining hall on an 80 acre campus.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E4
programme.desc: Piers Gibbon travels to Cameroon to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional Cameroonian medicine. Joining Piers are anxiety sufferer Jenna Patel and Dwight Werner, who has arthritis, back pain and sleep apnea, as they experience a range of extreme treatments. They are on a mission to find a potential cure that Western medicine has been unable to provide.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E4
programme.desc: The newest member of the community, Amanda's story illustrates how the Lawless Island community welcomes newcomers and guides them into self-sustaining Alaskans.

programme.desc: China has built some of the most impressive structures that have lasted the test of time, such as the Forbidden City and the Great Wall of China. But as the nation modernizes, so do its architectural needs and aspirations. Historian Sam Willis explores the history of Chinese architecture, the innovations and cultural considerations involved, and how it has evolved for the growing cities and future generations.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S9E1
programme.desc: As the season opens, Gloucester's elite get challenged by top new fishermen. Captain Bob Cook and his crew on Fat Tuna vow to dethrone reigning champion Dave Carraro on FV-Tuna.Com. Tyler on Pinwheel faces off with Krakens captain Sam Law who is out to settle a personal score, while Hot Tuna is the target of Wasabi co-captains Zack Plante and Charlie Boivin who believe they've got more grit than TJ Ott. The new contenders arrival tests the Gloucester fleet in ways they've never faced before as a heated battle for bluefin begins on the Atlantic Ocean.

programme.title: Mega Icons E4
programme.desc: Kiran Bedi, (born June 9, 1949, Amritsar, India), the first woman to join the Indian Police Service (IPS) and a social activist who was instrumental in introducing prison reform in India. Bedi was the second of four daughters. Her education included an undergraduate degree in English (1968), a master's degree in political science (1970), a law degree (1988), and a Ph.D. in social science (1993) with a focus on drug abuse and domestic violence. She joined the IPS in 1972 and went on to serve a variety of roles, including narcotics officer, antiterrorist specialist, and administrator. Bedi earned recognition for the work she did as inspector general of prisons, beginning in 1994. In that capacity she reshaped one of the largest prisons in the world-the Tihar prison complex, in Delhi-by addressing the corruption and human rights abuses she found there. She targeted sanitation and nutrition problems at Tihar and also implemented new literacy and drug treatment programs there. In.

programme.title: Inside T4: Terminal Of Tomorrow
programme.desc: In 2017, Changi Airport served a new high 62 million passengers. By 2030, it plans to bring its capacity to more 150 million passengers. The first step to this expansion is the opening of its new terminal - T4. With the annual world's Best Airport title up for review, Changi is pulling all the stops to elevate the flight experience from the moment a passenger steps into the terminal through the combination of nature, art and technology. From cutting-edge facial recognition technology to 12-metre-tall indoor trees and one the world's largest kinetic sculptures, we reveal how the team behind Changi Airport fuses innovative design and fully automated technological solutions to provide the airport experience Changi is world-renowned for.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E1
programme.desc: EasyJet, the UK's biggest airline, launched its largest ever pilot recruitment drive including a focus on encouraging more women to apply for this career where females currently make only three per cent of pilots worldwide. programme.desc: The Statue Liberty has welcomed millions of immigrants from all over the world to New York, creating a melting pot of different cultures. We visit the big apple's vibrant neighborhoods to sample a variety of foods this great big city has to offer.

programme.desc: After months at sea, adventurer Ellis Emmett's epic Pacific voyages lands him in the island nation of Kiribati, where he comes face-to-face with the realities of climate change, helps get a traditional sailing canoe back into the water, and befriends a king!

programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the remote corners of New Zealand's South Island on an adventure to discover the secrets of Maori cuisine.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E10
programme.desc: Local Chef and foodie Andrew Draper takes David on a culinary journey through his hometown of Durban, South Africa. Part of this food tour takes them up the coast to the beautiful Oyster Box Hotel, where David enjoys champagne to compliment fresh oysters harvested straight from the sea by the hotel manager himself. This culinary tour ends with a party and concert by the Durban Gospel Choir to celebrate Freedom Day, a national holiday in South Africa.

Liu Yong has led expeditions all over the world but he has always drawn back to Siguniang where he taught himself to climb ice falls 25 years ago. On this journey, Ben and Liu Yong learn how the local Jiarong Tibetan adapt to live in the high altitude environment and the duo eventually venture out into the wild to tackle a 300 meters ice waterfall at the altitude of 4,000 meters. Ben and Liu Yong put everything they have learnt to the test and challenge themselves beyond their limits.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E7
programme.desc: The famed Galapagos Islands teem with fantastic wildlife. The animals that could survive the long journey and harsh climate thrived in an isolated sanctuary. In this episode, we're taking a closer look at this healthy culture and seeing what the Hollywood life tastes like.

programme.title: Inside Turkish Airlines
programme.desc: This is a 360-degree view of operations for Turkey's biggest airline! They have thousands of travelers to transport, logistical nightmares to overcome, passengers to be intercepted and planes to be fixed. We follow their staff both in the air and on the ground – from pilots and flight attendants to baggage handlers and loadmasters, as they face the challenges of keeping a busy airline running.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E7
programme.desc: The famed Galapagos Islands teem with fantastic wildlife. The animals that could survive the long journey and harsh climate thrived in an isolated sanctuary. But that isolation left them vulnerable to the threats of the outside world. Now the islands' guardians reveal the hidden patterns of these endangered creatures with latest technology, and gain the critical insights needed to save them.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E5
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the Island of Maui, Hawaii, to explore the secrets of Hawaiian cuisine along the rugged Hana coastline.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E1
programme.desc: Kolkata, the first stop of Pablo's journey and the gastronomical capital of India. Pablo explores the streets, local markets and meets a lot of exciting people who give him a taste of Kolkata's gastronomy. Strolling in the market, collecting produce, Pablo decided to cook a fish, using techniques and produce he discovered in Kolkata.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E2
programme.desc: Monpa tribe- the other half of Brokpas are the farmers who reside in this small, beautiful village of Dirang. Always in barter with the Brokpas, Monpas people are farmers who grow a lot of corn.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E3
programme.desc: Reaching out to the most remote parts of Arunachal Pradesh, Pablo stepped foot on one of the far-flung valleys of Arunachal- The Lubrang Valley. Sheltering the Brokpa tribe and their yaks, Lubrang comes with very unpredictable weather. What kept Pablo warm at such high altitude is some delectable yak food and hospitality of the warmhearted Brokpas.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E2
programme.desc: Follow the rookie pilots as they take their first steps from the flight school classroom into the flight simulator, and on to flying large jets with hundreds of passengers on board. Meanwhile cadet Sophie Trunan learns how to deal with G-forces, and the firm's training captains jet off to France to showcase their skills to seven fledgling pilots.

programme.title: A Taste Of South Africa E1
programme.desc: Matt explores what cooking with fire means to modern South Africans and discovers that it is no accident that their cuisine is so deeply attached to cooking on fire as South African DNA and the very land they live on still glows with the flames of those who cooked before them. In order to explore his idea Mmakgomo Tshetlo takes Matt to Kwa Thema in Springs to try chisa nyama, township style street fired food.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S2E3
programme.desc: The Costa Deliziosa will soon be crossing the Suez Canal on her way home to Europe. Captain Pietro Sinisi has to balance his public appearances with duties on the bridge. Cruise Director is auditioning acts for a new show, and faces some difficult decisions regarding a sexy new artist. A popular stop is the stone city of Petra, and the crew looks forward to down time while passengers disembark.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E4
programme.desc: Ben and the crew arrive at Tasmania's East Coast to enjoy a night stay at the beautiful Thalia Haven Resort. Ben makes the most of their fully equipped kitchen and sets up to cook one of his favourite dishes, Asian Pork Belly. He explains how to prepare your pork belly with help from Andrew Stephenson.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E5
programme.desc: Ben Heads off to Bicheno Surf Life Saving Club to find out if there is any truth behind the myth of oysters being an aphrodisiac. He shows the best way to shuck an oyster while making a quick and easy dressing to accompany them. Ben heads back to the kitchen and shows his modern twist on an old classic, bread and butter pudding.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E6
programme.desc: Ben and the crew arrive down Tasmania's East Coast at the Avalon Coastal Retreat. Ben sets up on the deck with the picturesque view in the background and fires up the OzPig for to prepare a Lamb Rack with an anchovy dressing. Next Ben makes a quick and easy Apple Crumble using staples from his pantry to make a simple, yet delicious crumble. Ben explains, with some help from Melissa FItzgerald how to thicken your apple crumble sauce.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E19
programme.desc: Food has always been a way to spread joy and happiness for Pablo. When he got a chance to return the favour, Pablo couldn't think of a better way than to cook for the people of North East and share the magic of food with them. Pablo talks about his most innovative dishes given the limited amount of time and unusual ingredients, he churned out some amazing recipes in the North East of India.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E3
programme.desc: The colonial history of Sri Lanka is seen through its iconic colonial bungalows. The imprint of the Europeans on Ceylon was most evident with the spectacular Walauwas built for the powerful class that formed the bridge between the colonial administration and the locals. The fusion of European and local Sri Lankan architecture produced extraordinarily unique tropical mansions.

programme.title: Warrior Road Trip E3
programme.desc: Boni and Lemarti are two Kenyan warriors from the Maasai and neighbouring Samburu tribe. They have been best friends since they met during warrior training when they were teenagers. But Boni and Lemarti are no ordinary Maasai. They listen to hip-hop, ride motorcycles and speak three languages. Yet it's their roots as blood-drinking warriors that define them. On their journey Boni and Lemarti share their way of life with everyone they meet, enjoying the cultural exchange of ideas and showing us 'the way of the warrior'. Their simple, naturalistic approach to life collides with the fast paced mass-consumerist society of the West. As Boni and Lemarti struggle to get their heads around western culture, we reflect on our own choices and what we take for granted. Through the eyes of these ultimate outsiders, we see we are stranger than we think.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E11
programme.desc: Walking tours are all the rage in major metropolitan cities, and Durban is no different. Beset Durban is a free tour group operated by three young professionals, who take David on a private trek through their beloved city. They give David a crash course on some of the city's history, and check out some of the best local hotspots for delicious food. Through them, we learn about a city rich in culture and history, built on the backs of Indian immigrants, which is now currently experiencing an economic and social revitalization that you can feel on every street corner and with every food vendor.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E12
programme.desc: Lalibela Ethiopia, seems at first glance like a town lost to time, but with a closer look you can see that the economy is booming and the population is experiencing huge growth which is creating hope for a bright new future. David spends time with some of the locals to get their perspective on this bright future, while he learns how to make a few Ethiopian staples like Shiro, Injera and Berbere, the traditional Ethiopian spice mix that's a must in so many dishes.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce Africa E13
programme.desc: Nestled in the northern foothills of Ethiopia is the remote small town of Lalibela. It's considered one of the holiest places in the world, especially during the all-important Easter week celebrations. David takes in all the rituals and traditions, which date back over 1000 years, as he visits the beautiful monolithic churches, carved directly into the stone. A big part of Easter for the orthodox people of Lalibela is the 'breaking of the fast' after a 55 day period of Lent. David helps prepare for the traditional feast, with a visit to the huge Easter market, the slaughter, and finally, the preparations of the delicious meal which the entire family comes out to enjoy.

programme.title: Late Nite Eats S2E1
programme.desc: Jordan's in Memphis, a city known for BBQ and the Blues, but there's much more to its late night food scene. Jordan's firing up the evening with some Polynesian fare gone Southern at Atomic Tiki, a hidden tropical oasis in Overton Park. He whets his appetite with some pork belly steamed buns and gets a glimpse of their top selling favourite, the Polynesian meatballs before heading downtown.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E8
programme.desc: Fourteen Tanks. Twenty-seven reefs. One project. The South Florida Science Museum draws hundreds of thousands of visitors and they're building a new aquarium wing. The challenges are endless, from planning the displays, to constructing a shipwreck and balancing the different ecosystems perfectly, Living Colors next project is by far the most extensive yet.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S2E4
programme.desc: The Costa Deliziosa is heading for the Arctic Circle. Europe has been rocked by an outbreak of E-coli and a new Hotel Director has been brought on to enforce a sanitation programme. Australian Paul Huisintveld must settle in quickly as well as train a new Russian hostess. Franco, a dining room waiter with dreams of stardom, has been given permission to go all out in a dance routine.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E7
programme.desc: Ben arrives at one of his favourite community organisations, Produce to the People, on Tasmania's North-West Coast. He chats to Penelope, the founder of PTTP, and collects some fresh produce from around the farm to use in a recipe. He makes his version of lox and cream with a slight twist and some added pickled vegetables. Dr Mark Turner explains why pickling will preserve your fruit and vegetables.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E8
programme.desc: Ben prepares an Asian Chilli Chicken with the ingredients he found in Frankie the Food Truck and fresh produce from around the farm. While Ben's dish is simmering away, he has a quick chat with Penelope, the founder of PTTP, and discusses the importance of the organisation within the community. Next Ben makes a simple and healthy tartare, with a slight twist to the traditional.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E9
programme.desc: Ben arrives at the Pelican Point Sanctuary, down the East Coast of Tasmania. He sets up for a cook next to a beautiful stretch of water and prepares a fresh Salmon Tartare, paired with a vibrant, crisp salad. Next Ben makes a Raspberry Honeycomb, while Joel discusses what chemical reactions are taking place.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E5
programme.desc: Ariana travels to Tabriz, the birthplace of her father, who inspired her to be a chef. She visits some historic sites including the Grand Bazaar and Khaneh Mashrouteh where she meets a woman who runs a restaurant and is an example of the modern entrepreneurial Iranian woman. She also gets to satisfy her sweet tooth with qurabiya, a kind of almond macaroon that originates in Tabriz.

programme.title: A House Of Its Time E4
programme.desc: Geoffrey Bawa's fusion of colonial and local Sri Lankan architecture birthed Tropical Modernism and is indicative of a new independent Sri Lanka. Witness his clever use of light and space in a stable turned into a weekend home. Following in his mentor's footsteps, his apprentice, now a successful architect himself, built a home which pays homage to the past but looks to the future at the same time.

programme.title: Jose Andres: Dinner In Haiti
programme.desc: Join world-renowned chef Jose Andres on an exploration of Haiti, the most unknown country in the Caribbean. Along the way Andres experiences the authentic Haiti's traditions and rituals, from making cassava bread to midnight gatherings with vodou priests, and through its unique cuisine he discovers the history and culture, and sees into the future, of a proud and rarely understood people.

programme.title: Gordon Ramsay: Uncharted S1E5
programme.desc: Chef Ramsay travels to the Island of Maui, Hawaii, to explore the secrets of Hawaiian cuisine along the rugged Hana coastline.

programme.desc: Fabio Lisboa, a lifelong fish enthusiast, is looking to make his dreams come true. His vision is a 5000-gallon tank full of sharks. An aquarium that size will not only take up over half of his office, but will be the largest private tank in South Florida. As always, Living Color is up to the challenge.

programme.desc: Jordan's first stop in Charlotte is in NoDa, the city's vibrant arts district. He's kicking off his night at Haberdish, a North Carolina style southern kitchen and wine bar. Jordan's next stop is Uptown but underground, as he heads to The Cellar at Duckworth's.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E2
programme.desc: Clint flies in by sea plane to view the Grizzly Bears up close and also gets his hands dirty at Echo Valley Ranch in British Columbia.

programme.desc: For a lot of people, Tawang is synonymous with Buddhism. The ginormous Himalayas, a magnificent monastery, small houses with yellow tops and lamas in red robes makes Tawang very picturesque. Meeting and eating with the monks, paying regards at a centuries-old stupa of Zimithang, and cooking some favorite foods of the Nun are what Pablo's journey to Tawang all about.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E5
programme.desc: A beautiful laid back village in the remote areas of Ukhrul district of Manipur, Pablo landed here to meet the Thangkul Tribe. Welcomed by the very gentle king of the Thangkuls, Pablo shares his experience of having cockroaches and jungle squirrel for lunch. Later, he was invited over for a meal by someone who is not just an amazing cook but a very famous musician.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E6
programme.desc: One of the most iconic things in Darjeeling apart from the tea gardens is the toy train. After the train expedition Pablo met his host, with whom he enjoyed English breakfast at a place that was straight out of the British Era. Next stop is definitely the tea estate where he was enlightened by the tea master and Mrs. Chettri later invited Pablo to enjoy a very important dish- Gundruk.

programme.desc: After long hours, some close calls and way too much grunt work, the new guy Chris is tasked to lead a complete backyard makeover for his own company's Marketing Manager, Tony, and he's ready to prove he can make the grade in the pond business. Meanwhile, Ed and Greg take a field trip to a nearby high school to construct a courtyard pond to be used as a perfect outdoor classroom.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E2
programme.desc: The plains of Africa are home to nature's most fearsome predators: cheetahs, lions and hyenas. But the battle for survival is never one sided; even the prey can be formidable. We see a mother cheetah come face-to-face with the heavy weaponry of a Grants gazelle, and unpack what happens when three lions make the mistake of their lives and try to take down a pugnacious rhino.

programme.title: Snow Leopard Of Afghanistan
programme.desc: Nat Geo Wild joins the Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) and an international team of experts, including biologist Boone Smith, to set out on a mission in Afghanistan to find, capture and collar a snow leopard, and release it back into the wild. If they are successful, the expedition can offer a deeper understanding of the rare and beautiful species.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E2
programme.desc: Simon and Siouxsie get called to remove an angry black mamba from a huge wood pile. After 5 hours of searching they eventually find it, and it is seriously angry. A vicious spitting cobra spits venom like mad when Simon tries to get it out of a tree cavity, and it takes them almost a month to trap an elusive forest cobra that's been terrorizing trailer park residents!

With shark attacks on the rise, do these top predators see us as prey? Experts weigh in on some of the most amazing human-shark encounters captured on video to reveal the secrets behind the attacks.

programme.title: Freaks & Creeps E1
programme.desc: Lucy heads off to the rainforests of Borneo where countless strange creatures live. Her goal is get up close with the giant-nosed proboscis monkey. Along the way, she finds many other 'odd ones' that have come up with strange adaptations to survive in Borneo, like frogs that fly, a tarsier with eyes that are bigger than its brain and the wooly bat that makes its home in a carnivorous plant.

programme.title: Hunting The Hammerhead
programme.desc: Shark scientist Craig O'Connell is on a quest to reveal the predatory mysteries of the Great Hammerhead Shark. His aim is to uncover exactly how it hunts and unearth the secrets of its migratory behavior. Using a combination of technology, sheer guts and an unprecedented Hammerhead dissection, Dr. O'Connell and his team will shed new light on the unseen activities of this deep water predator.

programme.title: Hunter Vs. Hunted E2
programme.desc: This is a three-episode comp series that uses forensics-style investigations to explore wild animal attacks on people and why they happen.

programme.title: Predator Fail Compilation
programme.desc: Predators may have superpowers like venom, speed, and pack-hunting strategies, but prey species also have a few tricks up their sleeves. Some draw strength from numbers and others excel at swimming or climbing. See the classic conflict of predator versus prey in some timeless matches -- lion vs. warthog, crocodile vs. zebra, cheetah vs. gazelle -- through the eyes of the ones who often end up on the dinner plate...but not this time!

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E4
programme.desc: Ride shotgun with streetwise snake-catcher Simon Keys and sassy herpetologist girlfriend Siouxsie Gillett as they race across Snake City to save an office on lockdown after staff spot a green snake disappear under a door. Simon makes a gruesome discovery inside a shipping container after construction workers stumble upon a ten-foot black mamba, and Siouxsie handles a snake so lethal it can make you bleed from every orifice.

programme.title: The Monster Project E3
programme.desc: Judah Friedlander is in Texas to investigate the myths and legends of one of the most fascinating and elusive beings, the Chupacabra. So far all sightings have turned out to be coyotes, but is there any truth behind the legend?

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4.5 E1 !
programme.desc: Animal Fight Night presents another jaw-dropping adventure across the frozen landscapes of Scandinavia, the prehistoric jungles of Madagascar to the deadly deserts of Africa. In these treacherous terrains it's kill or be killed when angry elephants go on the rampage, hungry crocodiles fight ruthless lions and swarms of deadly ants battle to dismember each other - alive!

programme.desc: The Pond Stars head to the world-renowned Lincoln Park Zoo in downtown Chicago for two massive projects. First they come up with a solution to the Red Wolf exhibit whose pond has never functioned properly. While that's going on they also have a small rehab job to do on a water feature at the bird exhibit. What makes matters even harder is the Pond Stars have only 4 days to get it all done.

programme.title: India's Wild Leopards
programme.desc: India may be the land of the Tiger, but it is also home to masters of stealth that prowl the deepest of jungles and the highest of mountains. Journey to Ladakh in the Himalaya in search of Snow Leopards - the ghost of the mountains. Then venture into the realm of the smallest of big cats - the Clouded Leopard in the jungles of north east India. Wildlife Cameraman & National Geographic Fellow, Sandesh Kadur is on a mission to uncover their secretive lives.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S1E2
programme.desc: A small family of wild dogs is on the run, desperately looking for a safe place to raise their six puppies but the Savage Kingdom will test them to the limit. The sanctuary they seek is filled with rivals who stand in their way and predators that prey on their young. Only the resolve of their dedicated leaders, Teemana and Malao can save them.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn Compilations E2
programme.desc: Around the world, when the sun goes down, deadly dangers emerge. In the Arabian Desert, a gecko realizes he's not alone when the sand beneath his feet starts shifting. In Southern India, a praying mantis prays as an army of weaver ants march toward his arms and legs. In the African wilderness, a lion cub cries for his mother while a hyena gets closer, and closer. Who will survive the horrors of tonight, and who will be dead by dawn?

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E1
programme.desc: Biologist Zeb Hogan travels to Australia to try and track down two of the country's most dangerous river shark species - one thought to be the biggest, and the other possibly the rarest. First he tackles the mighty Bull Shark, a deadly predator capable of growing to the lengths of a small car. He then sets his sights on the Speartooth Shark, which has never had a confirmed sighting in the wild.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E3
programme.desc: Zeb heads deep into the Brazilian Amazon in search of an Electric eel large enough to kill a Caiman crocodile. He teams up with a local Amazonian fisherman to track and catch these elusive fish. If it's not too dangerous, Zeb wants to record the biggest electric shock he can without getting electrocuted.

programme.title: Predator Fail Compilation
programme.desc: Predators may have superpowers like venom, speed, and pack-hunting strategies, but prey species also have a few tricks up their sleeves. Some draw strength from numbers and others excel at swimming or climbing. See the classic conflict of predator versus prey in some timeless matches -- lion vs. warthog, crocodile vs. zebra, cheetah vs. gazelle -- through the eyes of the ones who often end up on the dinner plate...but not this time!

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S5E4 !
programme.desc: Isn't it bizarre to see animals defy their instinct and form unusual bonds with other species? You will be astonished by watching this episode. A goat doesn't like hanging out with its own kind but enjoys sharing food with a pig. Also a wrestling puppy loves hopping on the back of a pony and pulling off stunts with its best mate.

programme.title: Alaska Animal Rescue E3
programme.desc: There's a baby boom in Alaska! The rescue team from the Alaska SeaLife Center hits the road when a newborn sea otter gets separated from its mom. If this baby is alright, she'll require round-the-clock care. A new baby also arrives at the Alaska Raptor Center when a bald eaglet falls from its nest. But there's no time to rest. The team must also jump into action to save a stranded, injured eagle that's lost a fight. And at the Alaska Wildlife Conservation Center, two foxes rescued as kits are getting a habitat upgrade. But first they have to learn all the necessary tricks to make the big move.

programme.title: Man Vs Puma
programme.desc: In Patagonia, the pumas are killers. But even top predators start off as care free kittens. Big cat expert Boone Smith, follows a bizarre trail of carnage and death to track pumas in Patagonia. Boone travels to two top locations where puma behavior is unprecedented. In Chile, the prey is big and intimidating. In Argentina, the prey is much easier to capture?but it is something so unusual even Boone is surprised by it. The tables are turned when a big cat starts to stalk him and he comes face to face with a hungry mother on the hunt. Boone Smith is Walking With Pumas, and documenting their behavior - from kittens to killers.

programme.title: Shark Kill Zone
programme.desc: Sharks have remained mostly unchanged for the 400 million years they have lived on Earth. From body design to behavior, these are perfect predators that stalk, chase and attack prey in every sea on the planet using an extraordinary arsenal of deadly tools. There is no doubt they rule the seas, but what is the secret to their success? Enter the Shark Kill Zone and find out.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Brains And Babies E1
programme.desc: The early days for any species are precarious and survival depends perilously on the abilities of the parents, usually the mother. Take a closer look at the methods employed: stealth, cunning, disguise and poison, to protect the young from the stalking predators and marvel at the evolutionary adaptations that give newborns an essential edge to quickly learn how to survive once they're capable.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E6
programme.desc: After the death of her mother, Motshidi is starving and alone. In a terrifying reunion with her father, she has everything to lose. But in an uncharacteristic act of charity, Blue Eyes takes pity, giving Motshodi a new lease of life. A violent traitor rises in the rotten ranks, challenging the selfish princess and bringing an end to Mmamotse's rule. The Makulu Pack make one last stand as the battle for supremacy begins, but with the hyenas gone, it's up to Sega to lead the Matahta Pride to victory.

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E4
programme.desc: Zeb is in Guyana, South America in search of a fish with a terrifying reputation. Wolf fish, known locally as Haimara, are one of the most feared aquatic predators and are said to hunt both animals and humans. Said to be more ferocious than Piranha, Wolf fish can reach 1-meter long and nearly 100 pounds. With minimal info on them, Zeb heads into the Amazon to see if they deserve their reputation.

programme.title: Wild Argentina E1

Hes a resident of India the most populated part of the planet, and hes having to mix more and more with villagers. Its March in Indias Western Ghats, and that means one thing for King cobras - finding a mate. Having been dormant for the last few months, they are now fully alert and hot on the trail of female pheromones. The trail leads them right through a crowded village. Enter Gowri Shankar a snake expert who responds to calls from panicked villagers. Instead of beating the snakes to death, Gowri carefully captures them and takes them to a place of safety. Little is known about these highly venomous snakes. Previous research and tagging projects have only started to scratch the surface.
